### What problem does this feature solve?
Ability for app to trigger events when conditions are met async style.

### What does the proposed API look like?
In addition to mounted:

```
mounted : function() {
    // synchronous
    var table = this.$refs.myTable;  // will be undefined if it was loaded like        components : {  'my-tabe' : () => import(".../my-table.js") }
}
```

we should also have mounted.async:

```
"mounted.async" : async function() {
    // asynchronous
    var table = this.$refs.myTable;  // will be the actual table reference if it was loaded like         components : {  'my-tabe' : () => import(".../my-table.js") }
}
```

Essentially, whatever lifecycle hooks are applicable, should have an async version of it too, which only runs when all it's precondition resolves its promises. So the async mounted should only run when all it's child components have downloaded it's component and mounted it too.

The other benefit here is that the time between the regular mounted running and the async mounted running, you can also display a loading bar. 

Or an alternative is to make $refs async style

```
mounted : async function() {
    // asynchronous
    var table = await this.$refs.myTable;   // will be the actual table reference if it was loaded like         components : {  'my-tabe' : () => import(".../my-table.js") }
}
```

